<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}-{2}{y}=-{58}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}-{y}=-{64}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({7},{8}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --8. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{8}}{{-{{6}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{8}}}{{-{{6}}}}{\left(-{6}{x}+-{2}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{8}}}{{-{{6}}}}{\left(-{58}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{8}\right)}{x}+{2.6666666666667}{y}={77.333333333333}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}-{y}=-{64}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1.6666666666667}{y}={13.333333333333}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{13.333333333333}}{{1.6666666666667}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={8}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+-{2}{\left({8}\right)}=-{58}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{\left(-{16}\right)}=-{58}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}=-{58}-{\left(-{16}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}=-{42}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{42}}{{-{{6}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={7}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({7},{8}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>